reviewText: Interesting, about life of Eskimo people.  Kind of brief and not a sweeping description.

The time of simple documentaries like this one is long gone. It makes no political statements and does not blame anyone for native living conditions. This film shows an artic native family hunting, eating, and trading crafts at the trading post. This doc is free on you tube but if you have made that discovery too late it is worth the $4.99.
A look at a vanishing lifestyle of those who lived off the land and by their skill as good hunters.
